hands_on_practices.solution:
We have 
$$\mathcal{E}(n)=A\,n^2+B\,n^{5/2},\quad A=\frac{g+g_{12}}{4},\quad B=\frac{8m\,g^{5/2}}{15\pi^2\hbar^3}.$$
The pressure is
$$P(n)=n\frac{d\mathcal{E}}{dn}-\mathcal{E}
=n\bigl(2A\,n+\tfrac{5}{2}B\,n^{3/2}\bigr)-\bigl(A\,n^2+B\,n^{5/2}\bigr)
=A\,n^2+\tfrac{3}{2}B\,n^{5/2}.$$
Setting $P(n_{eq})=0$ for a self-bound droplet gives
$$A\,n_{eq}^2+\frac{3}{2}B\,n_{eq}^{5/2}=0
\;\Longrightarrow\;
A+\frac{3}{2}B\,\sqrt{n_{eq}}=0
\;\Longrightarrow\;
\sqrt{n_{eq}}=-\frac{2A}{3B}.$$
Since $g+g_{12}<0$ and $B>0$, the right-hand side is positive. Hence
$$n_{eq}
=\Bigl(-\frac{2A}{3B}\Bigr)^{2}
=\frac{4A^2}{9B^2}
=\frac{4\bigl(\tfrac{g+g_{12}}{4}\bigr)^2}{9\bigl(\tfrac{8m\,g^{5/2}}{15\pi^2\hbar^3}\bigr)^2}
=\frac{25\pi^4\hbar^6\,(g+g_{12})^2}{256\,m^2\,g^5}\,.
$$
